      "options": {
        "content": "## About This Dashboard\n\n**Project Alexandria** is a collaboratively maintained knowledge base of tooling setup guides, served via a **stdio MCP server** that runs locally alongside Claude Code.\n\n### Why docs-site probing?\n\nThe Alexandria MCP server (`mcp-server/index.js`) communicates exclusively via **stdio transport** — it exposes no HTTP port, no `/metrics` endpoint, and has no persistent host. It runs as a subprocess of Claude Code and cannot be directly probed by Prometheus or Blackbox Exporter.\n\nThe **GitHub Pages documentation site** (`https://7ports.github.io/project-alexandria/`) is the only publicly reachable HTTP surface of this project. Monitoring it serves as an operational health proxy: if the docs site is down, GitHub Pages infrastructure is degraded and guide updates cannot be published.\n\n### What is monitored\n\n| Signal | Source |\n|---|---|\n| HTTP uptime (UP/DOWN) | Blackbox Exporter → GitHub Pages |\n| Response time | Blackbox Exporter → GitHub Pages |\n| HTTP status code | Blackbox Exporter → GitHub Pages |\n\n### Extending monitoring\n\nIf Alexandria ever gains an HTTP API or web UI, re-run the Helldiver pipeline to add Alloy agent support and additional Blackbox probes.\n\n*Onboarded by Helldiver Squadron Beta · 2026-04-07*",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "About Project Alexandria Monitoring",
      "type": "text"
    }
